Reviews.Title: It's a great PC!
Reviews.Author: Cathy
Reviews.Content: I only wish this came with an option of Windows 7. But I managed to finally customize my Windows 8.The computer is very fast and it has all you need. I don't know another brand which offers such an amazing laptop at this price.

Reviews.Title: Dead In 24 Hours
Reviews.Author: Peder Kopperud
Reviews.Content: Massive disappointment.Disappointment in the equipment and disappointment in the seller.After reading all the great reviews and even speaking with friends that have MSI products I thought that this would be a great purchase as a Christmas gift.  Opened Christmas morning.  Less than 24 hours later it died and never came back on.  It simply shut off and never powered back up.I followed all the rules, requested a RA number returned the item at my own expense waited forever and than was notified that the return was refused because they claim the warranty sticker was tampered with.  Zero chance we tampered with anything.  This is BS.  So now I have this brick coming back to me and the only advice GizmoForLife can provide to me is for me to contact the manufacturer and go down that road.I filed a dispute with my credit card company and with the BBB.  I have been sold a lemon and than told to waste even more countless hours and money sending this *&^%$# brick back and forth between parties until it's fixed?Unless you like gambling NEVER buy anything from Gizmo's they will hose you in the end.

Reviews.Title: Excellent Gaming laptop
Reviews.Author: Switcher
Reviews.Content: I was a bit weary of buying this laptop over a dell, but I am impressed with it so far.Pros:The solid state drives are epic, allows it to boot up in about 12 seconds all the way to desk top.The keyboard with the 10 key on the side, the 3 color led backlighting is excellent.Battery life is about 3 hours, way better than my previous Asus G73Windows 8 - When i first got this laptop I hated Windows 8 so much, but after getting my start menu back I actually upgraded my desktop to windows 8.Beautiful screen.Fairly good sound, enough that you have to turn it down while gaming.Cons:Shipped with one dead pixel.PriceBack lit keys could be brighterI've had this laptop about 3 months now and wouldn't trade it for anything, except for one without a dead pixel.

Reviews.Title: Very nice machine
Reviews.Author: Stephen Tenhet
Reviews.Content: I won't repeat what others have said. I researched this machine before purchasing and it meets my expectations.I use hdmi. This high def video worked but audio did not. I had to update the drivers to get it to work. This machine replaced an ASUS Stealth machine which was easier to use out of the box. The MSI uses two video cards, which makes things a bit more complicated. Networking took a little extra effort.The MSI is lighter than the ASUS, which makes it easier to actually use on your lap! I like the 3.0 USB and rear connections for power video etc. The display is exceptional IMHO.I have been using this machine now for a few months and it plays all the games I've thrown at it. It handled the Windows 8.1 update with a little assistance. It is worth the money.

Reviews.Title: MSI GT70
Reviews.Author: SHB
Reviews.Content: This is an awesome computer. Everything I was looking for. I had been researching computers as I needed to upgrade my old Dell Inspiron as it was having difficulty with the 3-d modeling and analysis software I had been using. I had looked at computers from several different manufacturers and boutique sellers and finally settled on this MSI. Based on the power I was wanting as well as research I had done on customer satisfaction with the brand I decided on this computer. It has worked like a dream since day one and runs the modeling software like a boss. I would recommend this computer to anyone interested in a solid workstation or gaming rig. The keyboard feels clean and crisp, the system processing power is beast, screen is bright with good contrast. If I had one quibble it would be that the speakers don't have enough sound on the low end, meaning they don't push much bass, however the sound is still very good. Once again I would highly recommend this system to anyone looking for a great rig at a good price.

Reviews.Title: so far so good
Reviews.Author: road_king "road_king"
Reviews.Content: I like this pc a lot. i did upgrade it to win 8.1 which did require a lot of driver updates. So far I'm mainly using it at work and it's super fast and runs lots fo VMs.

Reviews.Title: nice computer
Reviews.Author: scrcmedic
Reviews.Content: This is a nice powerful computer. I use it for video and photo editing and it handles anything I can throw at it. no complaints I can think of

Reviews.Title: Awesome Computer!
Reviews.Author: kristina r whaley
Reviews.Content: I spent a great deal of time looking for a laptop that would replace my desktop without breaking the bank.  The GT70 20C-017US was the perfect fit!  It had the specs that I required and good reviews.Pros:Laptop was in perfect condition out of the box.  No dead pixels and it has been running smooth for the last couple of months.  This rig is perfect for gamming and anything else that floats your boat.Cons:Ad malware was immediately installed on the computer upon startup.  If this happens, download Ad-Aware to remove.  Also, immediately remove Norton and install ANY OTHER ANTIVIRIS!  I personally enjoy BitDefender.  Some complain that it is a memory hog, but it is because they do not know how to use it.Additional Notes:Be sure to remove any bloatware you are not likely to use.  I recommend using CCleaner for this type of job.  It's free and it does a nice job keeping the hard drive clean and the registry in check.Several owners of this laptop have also complained that it comes with Windows 8.0 and they have difficulty upgrading to 8.1.  Here is a hint, run all of the driver and Windows updates before installing 8.1.  This will save you on a lot of headaches.Many reviews have stated that this laptop runs hot.  The truth is...it does.  I recommend purchasing a docking station with extra fans to help with air flow.  In addition, if you are like me and wish to keep this laptop for a long time, you may want to use a separate monitor when docked to help spare the laptop's screen.

Reviews.Title: Great all around service
Reviews.Author: alex
Reviews.Content: Fast shipping, great product for the price. Definitely worth every penny for being a "refurbished" laptop because it is to the 99% original detail. Thanks for the gaming mouse!
